metadata.name: Intersection
metadata.description:
All alone on a dark and stormy night. The rumble of thunder fading in and out followed distant flashes. Gradually, they started getting brighter and the rumble soon turned to earth trembling booms. I stood in this same spot for what seemed like an eternity, but time was running out. Soon the rain will overtake me, and lightning will reach for the ground at a range too close for normal comfort and safety. My lights were set up and ready, the camera in place looking down the center of the road. With a single, powerful, cloud to ground strike it was over.

Artist: Tim Baca
ISO: 100
Fstop: 8
Shutter Speed: 13.0 seconds
Camera: Conon EOS R
Lens: EF16-35mm @35mm
